4markie:

Hmm… I did what soul said and now when I try to drop something nothing happens.

Where you see " // createGroundItem(droppedItem, absX, absY, c); " in your code is the problem. The // basically means whatever is to the right of it will not be read by the compiler, so logically removing the ‘//’ should fix your problem.
